<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10470377>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Geographic distribution and median-joining COI haplotype networks for Progoniada regularis Hartman, 1965 and P.cf. regularis Hartman, 1965. The colour-code in the network corresponds to the geographic localities, each vertical line represents one mutational step and the size of each haplotype its frequency.Haplotypes are numered 1–11, details are listed in the Supporting Information, Table S2. Available data came from both the Atlantic and Pacific Oceans; the type locality of P.regularis located off New England, NE Atlantic Ocean, is indicated by an asterisk in the map." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10470377/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10470397>
    dc:description "Figure 11. Progoniada cf. regularis Hartman, 1965, SEM and LM studies: A, macro- and micrognaths of proboscis. B, macrognaths.C, micrognaths.D, chevrons. E, proboscidial papillae stained with methyl green. F, prostomium, dorsolateral view.G, chaetigers 51–53, posterior midbody, leħ side, anterior view.—A–G, SMF 23791, Brazil Basin N. Scale Bars: A, 200 µm, B, D, F, G, 100 µm, C, E, 50 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10470397/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

